<p>Hi,</p>

<p>
  The automated BACS check ran on <strong><%= @run_date %></strong> but
  <strong>could not automatically submit the batch</strong>: some expenses need
  attention before proceeding.
</p>

<p>Please open the Review page and resolve the following:</p>

<table border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="4" style="border-collapse: collapse; font-family: sans-serif; margin-bottom: 1em;">
  <thead style="background-color: #f0f0f0;">
    <tr><th>#</th><th>Payee</th><th>Amount</th><th>Issue</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <% @issues.each do |issue| %>
      <tr>
        <td>#<%= issue[:auto_number] %></td>
        <td><%= issue[:payee_name] %></td>
        <td>&pound;<%= issue[:amount] %></td>
        <td><%= issue[:reason] %></td>
      </tr>
    <% end %>
  </tbody>
</table>

<% if @unblocked_count.positive? %>
  <p>
    <%= @unblocked_count %> other <%= "expense".pluralize(@unblocked_count) %>
    <%= @unblocked_count == 1 ? "is" : "are" %> ready and waiting for the above to be resolved.
  </p>
<% end %>

<p>
  Once every issue is resolved, submit the batch manually from Build Batch, or it will be picked
  up on the next scheduled check<%= @next_run_day ? " (#{@next_run_day})" : "" %>.
</p>

<p>Best,<br>Bedlam Fringe BACS (automated)</p>
